<kml>

<concept name=Attack-by-Fire>
<superconcept name=Attack>

<definition>

   an attack using direct fires, supported by indirect fires, to engage
   an enemy without closing with him to destroy, suppress, fix, or
   deceive him
  
</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is attacking by firing
     at the <slot>object</slot>
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=object>
     the target (a <conceptref name=Spatial-Entity>) that is being
     attacked
  </slotdescription>
  
</requiredslotlist>

<primaryslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=supported-by>
     the <conceptref name=Support-by-Fire> action that is supporting
     this attack
  </slotdescription>

</primaryslotlist>

<comment>
  
   The first <slot>subevent</slot> of this Attack-by-Fire is a 
   <conceptref name=Fire> by the <slot>agent</slot> <slot>toward</slot>
   the <slot>object</slot>
 
</comment>

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Bypass>
     Bypass is a military action by friendly forces in which a unit
     maneuvers around an obstacle
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Clear>
    Clear is a tactical mission task to remove enemy forces within an
    assigned area
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Follow-and-Assume>
     Follow-and-Assume is a tactical mission task to follow a force
     conducting an offensive operation and to continue the mission if the
     lead force is disabled
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Follow-and-Support>
     Follow-and-Support is a tactical mission task to follow and
     support a lead force conducting an offensive operation
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Occupy>
     Occupy is a tactical mission task to move a friendly force into
     an area and to control it
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Reconstitute-Unit>
     Reconstitute-Unit is a tactical mission task in which a military unit
     restores the full <slot>combat-strength</slot> of another unit
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Retain>
     Retain is a tactical mission task to ensure a terrain remains
     free of enemy occupation or use
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Seize>
     Seize is a tactical mission task to take possession of a designated
     area
  </neighbor>

  <neighbor name=Support-by-Fire>
     Support-by-Fire is a tactical mission task in which a maneuver
     force moves to a position where it can engage the enemy by direct
     fire in support of another maneuvering force
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


